        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-01-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="65"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                <head>65. Memorandum From the President’s Deputy Assistant for National Security
                    Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_SB3" type="from">Scowcroft</persName>) to the
                    Executive Secretary of the Department of State (<persName corresp="#p_PTR1"
                        type="to">Pickering</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d65fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>
                        Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 735,
                        Country Files, Africa, Burundi. Secret.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d65fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SB3">Scowcroft</persName> notified <persName
                            corresp="#p_PTR1">Pickering</persName> that the President had authorized
                        the Department to begin the normalization of relations with Burundi.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1974-01-29"
                        >January 29, 1974</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The President has authorized the Department of State to begin the normalization
                    of relations with Burundi. This normalization should commence with modest
                    allocation of resources in areas such as self-help assistance, population
                    projects, and cultural exchanges, and it should be understood that these steps
                    are predicated on continued evidence that the Government of Burundi is following
                    a national policy of respect for human rights.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SB3">Brent Scowcroft</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
